<figureCitation id="131C2A1A77697F4581AFA34BFF6DFA76" box="[151,242,1399,1426]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="101.[151,250,1715,1739]" captionTargetBox="[170,1410,187,1678]" captionTargetId="figure-19@101.[162,1425,181,1691]" captionTargetPageId="101" captionText="FIGURE 7. Dorsal view of males (except figures d and f) of: a) Belonuchus cifuentesi (paratype), b) B. dichrous (NHM©, Biologia Centrali-Americana), c) B. dichrous, d) B. flavipennis (female holotype shared by A. Kovalev©), e) B. flavipennis, f) B. iridescens (female holotype shared by A. Kovalev©), g) B. iridescens. Scale bars = 2.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630901" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630901/files/figure.png" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Figs. 7a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131C2A1A77697F4581C6A34BFEB6FA75" box="[254,297,1399,1425]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="114.[151,250,1910,1934]" captionTargetBox="[172,1414,182,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-25@114.[170,1417,181,1886]" captionTargetPageId="114" captionText="FIGURE 20. Male genital sternite of: a) Belonuchus cifuentesi, b) B. dichrous, c) B. flavipennis, d) B. aenigmaticus, e) B. iridescens, f) B. nigerrimus, g) B. optatus, h) B. platypterus, i) B. juanmorronei, j) B. abnormalis, k) B. pectinipes, l) B. viridipennis, m) Belonuchus sp. Q, n) B. cyanipennis, o) B. godmani. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630929/files/figure.png" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">20a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131C2A1A77697F45800CA34BFEC0FA75" box="[308,351,1399,1425]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="118.[151,250,1786,1810]" captionTargetBox="[164,1436,193,1751]" captionTargetId="figure-25@118.[151,1436,181,1762]" captionTargetPageId="118" captionText="FIGURE 24. Ventral (left) and lateral (right) view (except e) of the aedeagus of: a) Belonuchus rufiventris, b) B. xanthomelas (at center, detail of the apex of the median lobe), c) B. ephippiatus, d) B. moroni, e) B. cifuentesi (left: detail of paramere, right: ventral view; from Rodríguez and Navarrete-Heredia, 2016), f) B. dichrous, g) B. flavipennis, h) B. aenigmaticus, i) B. iridescens, j) B. nigerrimus, k) B. optatus, l) B. platypterus. Scale bar = 0.5 mm (all figures, except e)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630941/files/figure.png" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">24e</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131C2A1A77697F458053A34BFE0CFA75" box="[363,403,1399,1425]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="126.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[226,1359,191,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-25@126.[223,1363,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 32. Geographical distribution in Mexico and Guatemala of: a) Belonuchus cifuentesi, B. connexus and B. pectinipes; b) B. dichrous, B. iridescens and B. xanthomelas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630957" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630957/files/figure.png" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">32a</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33D651477697F4581AFA380FA8EF9A4" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8B98369F77697F4581AFA380FCA4FA37" blockId="70.[151,827,1467,1492]" box="[151,827,1467,1492]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<treatmentCitationGroup id="AB3711B177697F4581AFA380FCA4FA37" box="[151,827,1467,1492]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<treatmentCitation id="0A86108E77697F4581AFA380FCA8FA37" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6057818" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6057818" author="Rodriguez, W. D. &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, J. L." box="[151,823,1467,1492]" httpUri="http://treatment.plazi.org/id/1E78F453EC15FFF6FF04D4ABFB38D2B8" page="445" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" year="2016">
<taxonomicName id="4C274D1C77697F4581AFA380FCA8FA37" authority="Rodriguez &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, 2016: 445" authorityName="Rodriguez &amp; Navarrete-Heredia" authorityPageNumber="445" authorityYear="2016" box="[151,823,1467,1492]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cifuentesi">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D77697F4581AFA380FEEAFA30" box="[151,373,1468,1492]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Belonuchus cifuentesi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB64B6E77697F458043A380FCA8FA37" author="Rodriguez, W. D. &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, J. L." box="[379,823,1467,1492]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="444 - 450" refId="ref113932" refString="Rodriguez, W. D. &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, J. L. (2016) A new Mexican species of Belonuchus Nordmann (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). Zootaxa, 4083 (3), 444 - 450. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4083.3.8" type="journal article" year="2016">Rodríguez &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, 2016: 445</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B98369F77697F4581AFA03EFA8EF9A4" blockId="70.[151,1437,1538,2032]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
This species has been recently described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB64B6E77697F458347A03EFBA6F9F9" author="Rodriguez, W. D. &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, J. L." box="[639,1081,1538,1565]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="444 - 450" refId="ref113932" refString="Rodriguez, W. D. &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, J. L. (2016) A new Mexican species of Belonuchus Nordmann (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). Zootaxa, 4083 (3), 444 - 450. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4083.3.8" type="journal article" year="2016">Rodríguez &amp; Navarrete-Heredia (2016)</bibRefCitation>
; therefore, a redescription is not necessary. We only include some taxonomic comments and some illustrations of diagnostic structures.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33D651477697F4481FFA075FADFFEF9" lastPageId="71" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B98369F77697F4481FFA075FADFFEF9" blockId="70.[151,1437,1538,2032]" lastBlockId="71.[151,1436,151,429]" lastPageId="71" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D77697F4581FFA075FE54F980" bold="true" box="[199,459,1609,1636]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Taxonomic comments</emphasis>
. This species can be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D1C77697F458258A077FC7EF980" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1840" box="[864,993,1610,1636]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dichrous">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D77697F458258A077FC7EF980" box="[864,993,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">B. dichrous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D1C77697F458520A077FB2CF980" authorityName="Solsky" authorityYear="1870" box="[1048,1203,1610,1636]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D77697F458520A077FB2CF980" box="[1048,1203,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">B. flavipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The means of separation from 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D1C77697F458018A053FE3DF96C" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1840" box="[288,418,1646,1672]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dichrous">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D77697F458018A053FE3DF96C" box="[288,418,1646,1672]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">B. dichrous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mentioned in the taxonomic comments of that species. 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D1C77697F458502A052FAAEF96C" authorityName="Rodriguez &amp; Navarrete-Heredia" authorityYear="2016" box="[1082,1329,1646,1672]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cifuentesi">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D77697F458502A052FAAEF96C" box="[1082,1329,1646,1672]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Belonuchus cifuentesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D1C77697F45800FA0AFFE4BF948" authorityName="Solsky" authorityYear="1870" box="[311,468,1682,1708]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D77697F45800FA0AFFE4BF948" box="[311,468,1682,1708]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">B. flavipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the legs and first two visible abdominal segments reddish as elytra, male genital sternite very elongate (3.28 times longer than wide), aedeagus large (
<quantity id="4CDF9B7A77697F45853FA08AFBFBF934" box="[1031,1124,1718,1744]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
), oval-elongate shape, with apex subacute (
<figureCitation id="131C2A1A77697F45807AA0E6FE3EF910" box="[322,417,1754,1780]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="118.[151,250,1786,1810]" captionTargetBox="[164,1436,193,1751]" captionTargetId="figure-25@118.[151,1436,181,1762]" captionTargetPageId="118" captionText="FIGURE 24. Ventral (left) and lateral (right) view (except e) of the aedeagus of: a) Belonuchus rufiventris, b) B. xanthomelas (at center, detail of the apex of the median lobe), c) B. ephippiatus, d) B. moroni, e) B. cifuentesi (left: detail of paramere, right: ventral view; from Rodríguez and Navarrete-Heredia, 2016), f) B. dichrous, g) B. flavipennis, h) B. aenigmaticus, i) B. iridescens, j) B. nigerrimus, k) B. optatus, l) B. platypterus. Scale bar = 0.5 mm (all figures, except e)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630941/files/figure.png" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Fig. 24e</figureCitation>
). While 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D1C77697F4580C5A0E7FD0AF910" authorityName="Solsky" authorityYear="1870" box="[509,661,1754,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D77697F4580C5A0E7FD0AF910" box="[509,661,1754,1780]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">B. flavipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has legs and all abdomen black, except anterior border of sixth visible segment, male genital sternite short (2.21 times longer than wide), small aedeagus (
<quantity id="4CDF9B7A77697F458503A0C2FB3BF8FC" box="[1083,1188,1790,1816]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.13" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="1.13">1.13 mm</quantity>
), with elongate shape, convex apex, slightly acute in ventral view and moderately acute in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="131C2A1A77697F458517A11EFB0CF8D8" box="[1071,1171,1826,1852]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="118.[151,250,1786,1810]" captionTargetBox="[164,1436,193,1751]" captionTargetId="figure-25@118.[151,1436,181,1762]" captionTargetPageId="118" captionText="FIGURE 24. Ventral (left) and lateral (right) view (except e) of the aedeagus of: a) Belonuchus rufiventris, b) B. xanthomelas (at center, detail of the apex of the median lobe), c) B. ephippiatus, d) B. moroni, e) B. cifuentesi (left: detail of paramere, right: ventral view; from Rodríguez and Navarrete-Heredia, 2016), f) B. dichrous, g) B. flavipennis, h) B. aenigmaticus, i) B. iridescens, j) B. nigerrimus, k) B. optatus, l) B. platypterus. Scale bar = 0.5 mm (all figures, except e)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630941/files/figure.png" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4CDF9B7A77697F45855CA11EFB0CF8D8" box="[1124,1171,1826,1852]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.4" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" unit="g" value="24.0">24g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D1C77697F45859EA11EFA03F8D8" authorityName="Rodriguez &amp; Navarrete-Heredia" authorityYear="2016" box="[1190,1436,1826,1852]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cifuentesi">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D77697F45859EA11EFA03F8D8" box="[1190,1436,1826,1852]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Belonuchus cifuentesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also can be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D1C77697F458082A17BFDD2F884" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1915" box="[442,589,1863,1888]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arizonicus">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D77697F458082A17BFDD2F884" box="[442,589,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">B. arizonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According with 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB64B6E77697F458233A17AFB63F885" author="Rodriguez, W. D. &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, J. L." box="[779,1276,1862,1889]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="444 - 450" refId="ref113932" refString="Rodriguez, W. D. &amp; Navarrete-Heredia, J. L. (2016) A new Mexican species of Belonuchus Nordmann (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). Zootaxa, 4083 (3), 444 - 450. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4083.3.8" type="journal article" year="2016">Rodríguez &amp; Navarrete-Heredia (2016: 450)</bibRefCitation>
, “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D1C77697F45842BA17BFA03F884" authorityName="Rodriguez &amp; Navarrete-Heredia" authorityYear="2016" box="[1299,1436,1862,1888]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cifuentesi">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D77697F45842BA17BFA03F884" box="[1299,1436,1862,1888]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">B. cifuentesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognized by the black abdominal segments from tergite V, the pleurites VI and VIII are black in more than half of specimens, antennomeres pubescent, tempora less than twice as long as the length of the eyes, the first 4 antennomeres are longer than width, anterior corners and pronotal hypomera reddish-brown, frons with wide fovea and with a longitudinal impression, dorsal surface with scattered umbilicate punctures, first three antennomeres bearing only sparse strong setae, outer antennomeres (4–11) with microtrichia and long setae, profemur with two lines of spines of irregular size, metafemur with two lines of small and strong spines; tibiae with several spines; tarsi filiform, first and fifth tarsomeres longer than each one of the second to fourth, aedeagus small, narrow and elongate, median lobe subparallel-sided to slightly, evenly narrowed toward obtuse apex and smaller than 
<taxonomicName id="4C274D1C77687F448506A73FFB4DFEF8" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1915" box="[1086,1234,259,284]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Belonuchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arizonicus">
<emphasis id="B953EA8D77687F448506A73FFB4DFEF8" box="[1086,1234,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">B. arizonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="131C2A1A77687F4485D9A73FFABAFEF9" box="[1249,1317,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="103.[151,250,1906,1930]" captionTargetBox="[199,1392,191,1872]" captionTargetId="figure-19@103.[184,1404,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="103" captionText="FIGURE 9. Dorsal view of males of: a) Belonuchus sp. Q, b) B. cyanipennis (holotype), c) B. godmani. Head of B. dichrous showing the temporal carina (red arrow): d) lateral view (male), e) dorsal view (male). Dorsal view of the mandibles of males of: f) B. platypterus, g) B. viridipennis. Mandibles of Belonuchus sp. Q (male): h) dorsal view, i) ventral view. Antennae of males of: j) B. godmani, k) B. cyanipennis. Scale bars = 2.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6630907" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6630907/files/figure.png" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
)”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
